In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. declares that it is important for the national interest of the United States to provide assistance to refugees, victims of conflict, and other at-risk individuals as a result of the situation in Afghanistan. The assistance, which will not exceed $500 million, will be funded through the United States Emergency Refugee and Migration Assistance Fund. It can be provided through bilateral or multilateral means, including contributions to international organizations, funding to non-governmental organizations, governments, and US departments and agencies. The determination will be submitted to Congress and published in the Federal Register.